articles.author: Joseph Ax
articles.description: The dizzying presidential contest between Republican Donald Trump and Democrat Kamala Harris hurtled toward an uncertain finish as millions of Americans headed to the polls to choose between two sharply different visions for the country.
articles.title: Voters head to polls as turbulent campaign concludes

articles.author: Nidal Al-Mughrabi
articles.description: The Israeli military said, without giving details, that its forces had "eliminated terrorists" in the central Gaza Strip and Jabalia area.
articles.title: Israeli airstrikes kill at least 30 Palestinians in Gaza, medics say

articles.author: Tim Reid, Sarah N. Lynch
articles.description: Phony bomb threats that appeared to originate in many cases from Russian email domains targeted polling locations across several U.S. states on Tuesday, the FBI said.
articles.title: Hoax bomb threats linked to Russia target polling places in multiple states, FBI says

articles.author: Antoni Slodkowski, Liz Lee, Larissa Liao
articles.description: As Americans voted in one of the tightest presidential elections in decades, China braced for an outcome that - regardless of who wins - would spell four more years of bitter superpower rivalry over trade, technology and security issues.
articles.title: From Taiwan to trade, China braces for more rivalry as close US presidential race ends

articles.author: Rachel More
articles.description: German police have arrested eight suspected members of a neo-Nazi militant group driven by racist ideology and conspiracy theories who had been training in warfare for the downfall of the modern German state, prosecutors said on Tuesday.
articles.title: Germany arrests suspected members of neo-Nazi group plotting revolt

articles.author: Joshua McElwee
articles.description: Pope Francis on Tuesday paid a home visit to Emma Bonino, a veteran politician who successfully campaigned in the 1970s to legalise abortion in Italy, bringing her a bouquet of roses and chocolates.
articles.title: Pope pays house visit to veteran Italian abortion rights advocate

articles.author: James Mackenzie
articles.description: Yoav Gallant knew he was living on borrowed time as Israel's Defence Minister after Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu's first attempt to sack him last year failed in the face of some of the biggest protests ever seen in Israel.
articles.title: Israeli defence minister's sacking removes thorn in Netanyahu's side

articles.author: Andy Sullivan
articles.description: Republicans took a step toward winning control of the U.S. Senate with a victory in West Virginia on Tuesday, while neither party appeared to have an edge in the battle for the House of Representatives.
articles.title: Republicans pick up one seat in battle for US Senate; House control at stake as well

articles.author: James Oliphant
articles.description: White voters were on pace to comprise a larger share of the electorate than four years ago.
articles.title: Early takeaways from the US presidential election

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Hurricane Rafael is passing through the Cayman Islands in the Caribbean and is forecast to rapidly intensify before making landfall in western Cuba, according to the U.S. National Hurricane Center.
articles.title: Hurricane Rafael barrels through Cayman Islands
